---
description: "Common code style rules"
alwaysApply: true
appliesTo: ["**/*.html"]
priority: 1
---

- place empty line between sibling block-elements
- for long strings start every attribute from new line (or if >= 3 attributes)
- only short element definition could be one-line
- script, styles, link etc. group in blocks without empty lines  

```html

<body>
<div
    class="very-long-class-name-1 very-long-class-name-2"
    data-attribute-param="param-1"
    data-attribute-param="param-2"
>
    <p>Next li-elements is short</p>

    <ul>
        <li>Block first</li>

        <li>Block second</li>
    </ul>

    <p>
        <strong>Paragraph with long text couldn't be one line</strong>

        <br/>

        <span>Span elements is always one-line:</span>

        <span>Lorem ipsum dolor sit amet, consectetur adipisicing elit. Asperiores labore sunt veritatis. A ad architecto assumenda, cupiditate debitis deserunt dicta fugiat id illo incidunt, iste nemo nobis quas quasi saepe.</span>

        <a href="#">
            <i class="icon"></i>

            <span>link content</span>
        </a>
        
        <img
            class="class"
            src="http://..."
            alt="alt"
            title="title"
        />
    </p>
</div>

<!--groups in blocks without empty lines-->

<!--[start] scripts block-->
<script src="main.js"></script>
<script src="jquery.js"></script>
<script src="bootstrap.js"></script>
<script src="https://unpkg.com/alpinejs@3.13.3/dist/cdn.min.js" defer></script>
<!--[end] scripts block-->

<!--[start] styles block-->
<script src="main.css"></script>
<script src="bootstrap.css"></script>
<!--[end] scripts block-->
</body>
```
